Abstract Data Type

- A Description of the behavior of the data type without
  specifying its implementation details.

- Provides users of ADT with flexibility.

* Two Common ADTs
- Stack (LIF0 - Last in First Out)
    - Models a "stack of plates"
    - Operations:
        ~ push an element on the stack
        ~ pop an element off the stack
        ~ isEmpty() - check if the stack is empty

- Queue (FIFO - First in First Out)
    - Models a "line of people."
    - Operations:
        * Enqueue:
        * Dequeue:
        * isEmpty:

    Uses:
        - Files sent to a printer.
        - Threads.
        - Network packets waiting for transmission.
